This book contributes to our knowledge of this less familiar side of Ganesa. It describes his forms according to the Vidyarnavatantra, a large compilation on Mantrastra attributed to Vidyaranya.
The author is Professor of Sanskrit and South Asian religions in the dept. of languages and cultures of Asia, the University of Wisconsin-Madison, USA.
